  "prompt": "My birth date is 23\u201303-1994 , time 14:13, PLACE NEW DELHI. How will be my career and financial condition according to astrology?",
  "response": "To provide a detailed analysis of your career and financial condition based on your birth date, time, and place, an astrologer would typically create a natal chart (also known as a birth chart or horoscope). It includes the positions of the planets at the time of your birth and interprets them according to various astrological principles. Since I cannot create a chart, I can provide a general idea of what to consider regarding career and finance based on your birth data.\n\n1. **Sun Sign and Ascendant**: Your sun sign can reveal your core self and motivations. For someone born on March 23, 1994, your sun sign is Aries, which is often associated with traits like leadership, ambition, and a pioneering spirit. Depending on the exact time of birth and the calculation of your Ascendant (rising sign), your personality traits may further influence your career path.\n\n2. **Moon Sign**: The moon represents emotions and inner self. Your moon sign can indicate how you handle your emotions at work and your approach to financial decisions.\n\n3. **Midheaven (MC)**: The medium coeli or Midheaven point in your chart represents your career, public persona, and life goals. Analyzing its sign and any planets present can give insights into suitable career paths and potential challenges.\n\n4. **2nd House and 10th House**: \n   - The 2nd house governs personal finances, possessions, and values.\n   - The 10th house reflects career, reputation, and public standing. Strong placements and positive aspects in these houses can indicate financial prosperity and career success.\n\n5. **Planetary Placements**: The positions of Mercury (communication), Venus (finance and values), and Jupiter (growth and luck) can significantly affect your career and financial situation. Beneficial aspects (like trines and sextiles) can indicate ease in these areas, while challenging aspects (like squares and oppositions) might suggest obstacles.\n\n6. **Transits and Progressions**: Current astrological transits can impact your career and finances. Significant planetary movements in relation to your natal planets can indicate periods of opportunity or challenges in these aspects of your life.\n\nFor a precise, personalized interpretation, it's best to consult an astrologer who can analyze your complete natal chart. They can provide detailed insights and predictions based on astrological methodologies.",
